docs.abstract: The moves could hamstring the Chinese tech giant, escalating a cold war between China and the United States over technology and trade.
docs.snippet: The moves could hamstring the Chinese tech giant, escalating a cold war between China and the United States over technology and trade.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The Chinese technology giant Huawei on Monday began to feel the painful ripple effects of a Trump administration order that effectively bars American firms from selling components and software to the company, ramping up a cold war between the two countries over technology and trade.

headline.main: U.S. Tech Suppliers, Including Google, Restrict Dealings With Huawei After Trump Order

byline.original: By Adam Satariano, Raymond Zhong and Daisuke Wakabayashi

docs.abstract: The deal ends Sports Illustrated’s ties to its former owner, Meredith, a few weeks after the Authentic Brands Group bought the magazine’s intellectual property.
docs.snippet: The deal ends Sports Illustrated’s ties to its former owner, Meredith, a few weeks after the Authentic Brands Group bought the magazine’s intellectual property.
docs.lead_paragraph: The digital platform company TheMaven has bought the right to publish Sports Illustrated — digitally and in print — for at least the next 10 years, ending the former owner Meredith’s relationship with Sports Illustrated a few weeks after the landmark magazine’s intellectual property was sold to the Authentic Brands Group, TheMaven and Meredith announced Monday.

headline.main: Sports Illustrated Has a New Publisher, Digital Company TheMaven
headline.print_headline: Digital Company Buys Right To Publish Sports Illustrated

docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve left interest rates unchanged but opened the door to a future rate cut if risks to economic growth intensify.
docs.snippet: The Federal Reserve left interest rates unchanged but opened the door to a future rate cut if risks to economic growth intensify.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump might get what he wants from the Federal Reserve, which kept interest rates steady on Wednesday but indicated that it could soon cut them as economic risks mounted and inflation remained stuck below target.

headline.main: The Fed May Give Trump His Rate Cut. The Question Is When.

docs.abstract: A number of shoe companies have cut off many small retailers that were already struggling to adapt to shoppers’ changing behavior.
docs.snippet: A number of shoe companies have cut off many small retailers that were already struggling to adapt to shoppers’ changing behavior.
docs.lead_paragraph: BELFAST, Me. — Colburn Shoe Store, established in 1832, advertises itself as the oldest shoe store in the country. It has occupied the same small storefront on Belfast’s Main Street since 1905. It’s a place where the owner, Colby Horne, and his father, Brian, remember the brand and size their customers like, and those of their children, their partners and probably their siblings, too.

headline.main: Shut Out by Shoe Giants, ‘Mom and Pop’ Stores Feel Pinched
headline.print_headline: Shut Out by Shoe Giants, Small Stores Feel Pinched
